The paper deals with real-time video broadcast over wireless networks, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The use of network coding for video transmission also falls under the category of multimedia (MM) and distributed computing (DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the formulation of a packet selection problem, which can be categorized under social and information networks (SI).
